<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Wentzel, Willard Ferdinand. A Continuation of the Journal of the Forks Mackenzie's River for Summer 1807-1808. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0022</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p></p>
<p class="head">September 1807 Continued</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Friday 12<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Fine weather<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent off the forgoing to look out some Place where he can make Traps to Kill B<sup>r</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Satu<sup>y</sup> 13<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  My Hunter returned to day with a B<sup>r</sup> &amp; sett off again to join the Robe de Castor in seeking for B<sup>r</sup> Lodges &#8211; brought also two bustards<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Sun<sup>y</sup> 14<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Rained all last night<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Since the 5<sup>th</sup> the Gibiers have been continually passing in great Flocks tho' none lights near the Forks &#8211; Swans, Grey Geese &amp; Bustards<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Mon<sup>y</sup> 15<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Arrived three Indians from <span style="text-decoration:underline;">River au Peau de Lievre</span><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>hese brought 26 Skins furrs &amp; 10 in Prov<sup>ns</sup> these have payed me visits already three times<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Traded with &amp; sent them off<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tues<sup>y</sup> 16<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[N]</span>othing Strange transpired to day<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Wedn<sup>y</sup> 17<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Capot Rouge Shewed himself to day with 5 Skins of Fresh meat<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Complains heavily that there are no tracks of Animals &#8211; &amp; but few beavers to be Killed<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[H]</span>e even Cryed saying that he would be pitiful this winter &#8211; &amp; that he feared that he Should not be able to find subsistance for the Fort<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[H]</span>e asked me to lend him a few Orignal Collets which he intends to set as the rutting Season is soon at hand &#8211; thinking that some Stragling moose may ensnare themselves in the Snares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Thurs<sup>y</sup> 18<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent off the Capot Rouge gave him 3 meas<sup>s</sup> Am<sup>n</sup> &amp; desired him to do his best to find out either Animals or Beaver for that I was quite out of Prov<sup>ns</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Friday 19<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  My young man returned &amp; brought 1 Cascameat &amp; 2 Swans<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Satur<sup>y</sup> 20<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Water in the Forks and Grand amazing low<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  My Hunter remained here all day<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Sun<sup>y</sup> 21<sup>st</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent off my Hunter to his B<sup>r</sup> Traps<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Mon<sup>y</sup> 22<sup>nd</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the afte<span class="AddHand-author">r</span>noon arrived M<sup>r</sup> Henry in a Saulteux Canoe with his Family and a Jack Montagnier &#8211; from Athabasca<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[H]</span>e left that Place on the 19<sup>th</sup> of August &#8211; but has always been detained by contrary winds bad weather &amp;<sup>c</sup> &amp;<sup>c</sup> according to his own Accounts<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  News from Fort Chipewean says that 694 Packs had been shipped off for Lac La Pluie last Spring<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Grand River Packs observed to be too light by 2<sup>lb</sup> each<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  This deficiency in the weight of our returns I cannot account for, as they were weighed in the Same balances &amp; by the Same weights as those of last year &#8211; of which no com-</p>

